==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: crookneck
<hw>crook"neck`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Either of two
varieties of squash, distinguished by their tapering, recurved necks.
The <stype>summer crookneck</stype> is botanically a variety of the
pumpkin (<spn>Cucurbita pepo</spn>) and matures early in the season. It
is pale yellow in color, with warty excrescences. The <stype>winter
crookneck</stype> belongs to a distinct species (<spn>Cucurbita
moschata</spn>) and is smooth and often striped.</def> <mark>[U.
S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> crookneck squash.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Croquante</ent>⟦br⟧
